Project Overview
This project performs exploratory data analysis on retail sales data. You analyze sales, customers, and products to uncover patterns, trends, and insights that support data driven business decisions.

Project Objectives
You explore sales performance over time.
You analyze customer demographics and purchasing behavior.
You identify high and low performing products.
You generate insights that support retail strategy.

Datasets
Dataset 1. Retail sales data.
Dataset 2. Additional retail or customer data.
Replace the placeholders with the actual dataset links.

Key Concepts and Tasks
• Data loading and cleaning. Load datasets and handle missing values, duplicates, and errors.
• Descriptive statistics. Calculate mean, median, mode, and standard deviation.
• Time series analysis. Analyze sales trends over time.
• Customer and product analysis. Study demographics, behavior, and product performance.
• Data visualization. Use bar charts, line plots, and heatmaps to present insights.
• Recommendations. Provide actionable business recommendations based on findings.

Tools and Technologies
• Python
• Pandas
• NumPy
• Matplotlib
• Seaborn
• Google Colab

Learning Outcomes
You gain hands on experience with data cleaning and EDA.
You improve your ability to interpret statistics and trends.
You learn to communicate insights using visualizations.

How to Run the Project using Google Colab
• Open Google Colab in your browser.
• Click New Notebook or open the notebook directly from GitHub.
• Upload the dataset files or mount Google Drive.
• Run the notebook cells from top to bottom.
